Section 10: RSPEC

Vocabulary:
  Gem: a self contained ruby program / library
  Bundler: manages the development environment for a project
    - creates a locked version of each gem in the Gemfile
    - this allows others to download the project and get the same results

Key Concepts:
  Basic File Hierarchy:
    FOLDER/
    |- lib/ (actual code)
    |- spec/ (testing files)
    |- Gemfile
    |- Gemfile.lock

Keywords:
  gem install bundler - installs the bundler gem (just do this once per computer)
  bundle install - installs the gems from the gemfile (do once per gemfile update)
